Rezept Roastbeef mit KrÃ¤uterkruste:

SemmelbrÃ¶sel

ZunÃ¤chst das Roastbeef mit Salz einreiben und dann von allen Seiten kurz anbraten und anschlieÃŸend in den Ofen. Entweder fÃ¼r 180Â°C und 20 Minuten oder 80 Â°C und 2 Stunden. Dazwischen ist alles mÃ¶glich. Ihr kÃ¶nnt also entweder niedergaren bzw niedrig garen oder eben die schnelle Variante wÃ¤hlen. Wenn ihr keine Erfahrung mit Fleisch habt empfehle ich definitv ein Thermometer dass ihr auf eine Kerntemperatur zwischen 50-55Â°C abzielt. In der Zwischenzeit die KrÃ¤uterkruste vorbereiten indem ihr die KrÃ¤uter kleinhackt und mit den SemmelbrÃ¶seln, der Butter sowie dem Senf vermischt. Nachdem das Roastbeef die Kerntemperatur erreicht habt, tragt ihr die KrÃ¤uterkruste auf und stellt den Backofen auf Grillen (Oberer Grill) und schaut dass ihr die Kruste so kurz gratiniert. AnschlieÃŸend das Roastbeef noch ca 5 Minuten ruhen lassen, danach erst aufschneiden.

Rezept Sauce / SoÃŸe:

Zwiebeln und Knoblauch fein hacken und anschwitzen. Zucker hinzugeben und karamellisieren lassen. Mit ordentlich Kalbsfond und Portwein ablÃ¶schen und die FlÃ¼ssigkeit reduzieren lassen. Je mehr, desto besser und desto dicker wird eure Sauce (Das braucht viel Zeit!). Sauce ist nicht umsonst teuer und Zeitintensiv. Sobald die gewÃ¼nschte Konsistenz erreicht ist die Sauce passieren (durch ein Sieb geben).

Rezept Speck-Bohnen:

Bei den Speck-Bohnen einfach die Spitzen abschneiden und die Bohnen kurz in etwas BrÃ¼he blanchieren. D.h. kurz kochen lassen und dann in Eiswasser geben. Die so balnchierten Bohnen mit Speck umwickeln und in einer Pfanne braten. Wahlweise mit etwas Butter fÃ¼r ca. 10 Minuten bei 180Â°C in den Ofen.

Rezept Violetter Kartoffel-Espuma:

Die Kartoffeln schÃ¤len und in Salzwasser kochen. Es ist normal, dass sich das Wasser dabei grÃ¼n verfÃ¤rbt (Stichwort natÃ¼rlicher Indikator). 250g der Kartoffeln zusammen mit 200mL Sahne und 100mL Kartoffelnwasser pÃ¼rieren. Dazu etwas Butter, Muskatnuss sowie Salz und Pfeffer geben. Die Masse passieren und in das SahnegerÃ¤t mit 2 Patronen laden. In einem Wasserbad warmhalten.

Rezept: Violetter Kartoffelstampf:

Genau wie beim Espuma nur ohne Sahne und Kartoffelwasser. Nicht pÃ¼rieren sondern lediglich stampfen. Nicht passieren.

title: Ultimate Bacon Recipes
tags: Tasty|"BuzzFeed"|"BuzzFeed Tasty"|"bacon"|"recipes"|"bacon recipes"|"chicken"|"bacon ring"|"beef"|"bbq"|"meatball"|"bacon wrapped meatball"|"bacon burger"|"burger"|"cheese burger"|"food"|"cooking"|"grilling"|"skewers"
description:
Buy the Tasty Cookbook Today: http://bit.ly/2zVLRydÂ 

Here is what you'll need!

INGREDIENTS
3Â½ cups of ground chicken breast
1 cup of flour
2 eggs
1 chopped onion
2 cloves garlic, minced
1 tablespoon of salt
Â½ tablespoon hot pepper
5 oz of cream cheese
Â¼ cup chopped parsley
Â¼ cup chives
1 can of corn
Â½ cup of mozzarella
22 slices of bacon

PREPARATION
1. Preheat oven to 350ËšF (180ËšC)
2. In a bowl, combine chicken, flour, eggs, onion, garlic, salt and pepper until smooth. Reserve.
3. In another bowl combine the cream cheese, parsley, spring onion, corn and potatoes until smooth.
4. Arrange the bacon slices in a round shape, leaving the tips out.
5. Place the chicken stuffing underneath and on the sides. Save a portion for the top.
6. Add cream cheese paste and spread well.
7. Put the rest of the chicken, close with the bacon tips and cover with foil.
8. Bake for 30 minutes
9. Remove the paper and leave it for another 30 minutes
10. Remove from oven, let stand for 10 minutes, then uncover.
11. Enjoy!

title: National Clean Out Your Fridge Day with Matt | Fidel Gastro
tags: clean out your fridge|"leftovers"|"holdiay leftovers"|"bread bowl"|"italian food"|"salami"|"olives"|"sun dried tomatoes"|"national clean out your fridge day"|"fridge leftovers"|"leftover fridge food"|"fidel gastro"|"matt basile"
description:
Many of you our there probably have no idea that there is in fact a specific day recognized throughout most of the world to clean out your fridge. Matt takes this opportunity to pull out some of the extras from his own fridge and whip up a creative and delicious looking dish. 



National Clean Out Your Refrigerator Day is observed annually on November 15th, just before Thanksgiving. This is perfect timing as you're going to need plenty of room for leftovers. For most of us cleaning out the fridge is a dreaded task. We will make excuses, find other easier chores, or even just pretend we don't know it needs to be cleaned out to avoid having to do it. However, ignoring the problem doesn't make it go away. 

Research has found that National Clean Out Your Refrigerator Day was created by the home economists at Whirlpool Home Appliances way back in 1999.  It is said that they originally created the holiday to encourage people to clean out their refrigerator prior to the upcoming holidays.  At the time, the company even had a toll-free hotline that people could call in to for tips on dealing with the task. 

Upon opening his fridge Matt finds a plethora of items that need to be used or discarded. He pulls out hot sauce, some chives, olives, tomatoes, white onions, salami, mushrooms, a loaf of bread, wine, shredded cheese, and even a Darth Vader head. When he puts it all out on the counter in plain site and you get a good look at the pile you really see how much extra food Matt had in his fridge. His collection will no doubt cause you to ask yourself if you could pull a similar sized pile out of your own fridge. 

After accessing the ingredients at his disposal Matt notices an Italian theme emerging and decides to use his ingredients to make what he calls a hybrid pizza sandwich thing.

He starts off by combining sun dried tomato oil, white onion, capacolla, fresh tomato, pickled vidalia onions, giardineira, and red wine into to medium sized pot on high heat. He stirs this frequently as it cooks and adds in a bit of tobasco as well as the chopped mushrooms he found. Next he smashes and then dices the olives he foraged and adds them into the mix. He adds in some leftover tomato sauce as well as the sun dried tomatoes he drained the oil out of earlier. He then grates a fair amount of parmesan cheese into the newly created sauce and turns down the heat to let it slowly cook the rest of the way.

While the sauce simmers Matt takes his loaf of bread and cuts the top off of it. He then carefully cuts out the bread from the center of the loaf creating what is commonly known as a bread bowl. 

In the very bottom of the bread bowl he lays down a layer of salami. The salami has a dual purpose, the first being flavor and the second being protection. The salami is thick enough to prevent the sauce from seeping through the bottom of the bread bowl. On top of the salami he adds a good amount of the shredded cheese he purloined from the fridge and follows that up with a thick layer of the sauce he just made. He makes it clear at this point that you really want to pack that sauce in there super tight. Once he has the sauce added he tops it with an additional layer of salami. After the salami layer is done he adds even more shredded cheese to the top of it and fills the remaining space in the bread bowl with sauce. 

Matt recommends applying the sauce while it's still warm as this will greatly aid in melting the cheese, and trust us you want that cheese melted.  Top your sauce with one more layer of shredded cheese and add some freshly grated parmesan to it. 

Now that you have a 6 layer bread bowl full of delicious ingredients it's time to bake. Preheat your oven to 375' F and place this bread bowl right on your oven rack without the lid on it. You will know that your hybrid pizza sandwich thing is done when it reaches a slightly crispy, lightly browned color around the top as seen in the video. Carefully remove it from the oven, add some additional shredded parmesan to the top, garnish with chives,  and finally a bit of canola oil.

There you have it. A masterful creation from the foods in Matt's fridge that may have very well gone to waste. Think of all the food hiding in your fridge that you could turn into a spectacular meal in no time flat. 

For more fantastic recipes and cocktail concoctions be sure to subscribe to the Fidel Gastro YouTube channel and as always thank you for watching.

title: Open Concept Tiny House with Clever Custom Furniture - Off Grid Home Tour
tags: tiny|"house"|"tour"|"tiny house tour"|"interior"|"design"|"off"|"grid"|"off the grid"|"off-grid"|"solar"|"power"|"panel"|"wood"|"stove"|"woodstove"|"heat"|"winter"|"insulation"|"micro"|"cabin"|"cottage"|"wheels"|"trailer"|"mobile home"|"RV"|"nomadic"|"home"|"soy"|"spray"|"foam"|"inside"|"Canada"|"Cabane"|"mini maison"|"mini"|"maison"|"Quebec"|"2018"|"new"|"beautiful"|"space"|"saving"|"furniture"|"loft"|"minimalist"|"small"|"living"|"lifestyle"|"DIY"|"build"|"exploring"|"alternatives"
description:
Kate and Simon built this 250 square foot off-grid Scandinavian-style tiny house as a cottage and have since started building tiny houses as a family business.

To find out more about their tiny house construction, you can check out the Cabane website here:
http://minicabane.com/

This tiny house is 8.5 feet wide, 13 feet tall, and 20 feet long.  It's been designed to be fully off-grid with a solar panel and 12-volt battery bank for power, propane for the stove and water heater, and a cubic mini wood stove for heat.

They used a soy-based spray foam insulation, and a natural oil finish for the interior wood finish.

We love all the space saving furniture they custom designed for their tiny house, and all the thought that went into making it a functional space for the couple and their young son.

The kitchen is massive with loads of storage space and countertops, and they did it without having overhead cabinets which gives the space a nice open concept feel.

The loft is quite spacious and can accommodate a queen-sized bed, and also has built-in storage and night tables, as well as a window for ventilation.

In the bathroom they have a 30x30 inch shower, a dry bucket-style toilet, and they have a grey water tank.

With the sliding patio doors leading onto a spacious deck, this tiny house merges indoor and outdoor living space seamlessly.

Thanks for watching!

Mat & Danielle

Taking apart the Essential phone is pretty similar to the Google Pixel. Except for the fact that there are no replacement parts available for this smartphone. title: How to make a Wooden Katana from hardwood flooring // Woodworking
tags: katana|"samurai"|"samuri"|"sword"|"samurai sword"|"flooring"|"hardwood flooring"|"woodworking"|"how to"|"wooden katana"|"from hardwood flooring"|"how-to"|"make"|"diy"|"teak"|"blade"|"iltms"|"i like to make stuff"|"bob clagett"|"ninja"|"ninja sword"
description:
I was inspired to make a wooden katana using left-over hardwood flooring! 
Subscribe to my channel: http://bit.ly/1k8msFr
Second Channel: http://bit.ly/iltms-2

Check out Alec Steele's series: https://youtu.be/0eeWUw59GYk
Check out Geeks Wood Shop katana build: https://youtu.be/pSjzORXq2AQ

MORE PROJECTS, POSTS AND EVENTS
http://www.iliketomakestuff.com

TOOLS & SUPPLIES:
https://kit.com/iliketomakestuff/my-woodworking-tools
https://kit.com/iliketomakestuff/shop-safety-gear

Want to support ILTMS? Get exclusive content and more... 
http://www.iliketomakestuff.com/patreon

BUY A SHIRT, STICKER, DIGITAL PLANS and MORE!!
http://www.iliketomakestuff.com/store

FOLLOW:
http://twitter.com/iliketomakestuf
http://www.twitch.tv/iliketomakestuff
http://instagram.com/iliketomakestuff
http://facebook.com/iltms

I have always been intrigued by martial arts and after watching Iron Fist on Netflix I had the idea of making my own practice katana. I had a lot of scrap hardwood flooring from our home renovations, so I found some really beautiful pieces and got to work.
Most of the sword is made from left over cumaru teak flooring that I recently used in our house. It has a really beautiful grain pattern and some elegant figuring, plus it's extremely dense and hard. I had just finished watching Alec Steele's series on making a Damascus steel katana, so I had a rough idea on how the whole thing went together.

First, I drew out the rough shape of the blade based on some online dimensions. I cut out this shape on the bandsaw making sure to leave a tang on the bottom that would fit inside the hilt. I rough sanded the blade to give the sword some definition and moved on to the tsuba, or hand guard.

I found another smaller piece of teak flooring for the tsuba. I used some calipers to measure the tang dimensions and transferred those lines to the blank tsuba. I drilled out this space and had to chisel and file the pocket very carefully so that the blade tang would sit snuggly into it. After I had a good fit, Â I cut the tsuba into an oval using a paper template.

After researching how katana hilts are wrapped in cotton or silk strips, I decided to recreate that look with an inlayed contrasting wood. I had a piece of scrap oak flooring from my boys' room which would look awesome against the teak hilt. While I worked on other projects, I had my friend Josh CNC out the hilt design and the resulting diamond pattern looked just like a traditional fabric wrap.Â I hogged out the inside of the hilt to receive the tang and once I got a snug fit, it was time to assemble the major components.

The tsuba fit onto the tang and the tang fit into the hilt. I added a kashira or pommel to the end of the hilt and it was all done. I finished the katana with some linseed oil and beeswax polish and it looks gorgeous! I am so happy to have my own sword and I feel like a true samurai!

If you liked this woodworking prop, check out the playlist above for more!

title: Chapter 28: I Love My Baby But, I Miss My Dad
tags: Whitney Port|"I Love My Baby But"|"Grief"|"Grieving"|"Death of a Parent"|"Parenting"
description:
***We are having technical difficulties with the video! So sorry! Iï¸t will be back up and running soon! 

As some of you may know, I lost my dad to kidney cancer almost 5 years ago. It has been a traumatic and grief filled world for me for so many reasons. Simply put, he was my dad. He was the main man in my life for almost all of my life and really ruled at it. I miss him every single day. More recently, really since Sonny was born, I find myself missing him more and more. Itâ€™s unfortunate how such amazing times in ones life, like getting married or having a baby, can be colored with such darkness. Again, I hate to be a total downer, but this is the reality of so many of our lives. This doesnâ€™t mean we love our husbands or our babies or even our whole lives any less, itâ€™s just that itâ€™s difficult to fully feel pure happiness at these momentous occasions. Sometimes Iâ€™m ridden with the simple thought of how much better life would be with my dad and that just makes me so sad. Once I  get to that dark place though, my mind has the ability to take a turn and see not only how lucky I am for what I have, but how lucky I was to have a parent that taught me how to be a good parent in return. In this Chapter of I Love My Baby, But I Miss My Dad, we cover missing my dad, honoring my dad and passing on the lessons he taught me so his legacy lives on and on and on. He deserves that. Iâ€™d love to know how any of you out there who have lost parents have taught your children about them and kept the spirit of them alive. Comment below. Love you all.

Abtreibung: Ariane will herausfinden, was auf eine schwangere Frau wirklich zukommt, wenn sie abtreiben mÃ¶chte. Von der ersten Recherche im Internet bis zur FrauenÃ¤rztin, die den Abbruch durchfÃ¼hren wÃ¼rde.

Ob eine Abtreibung in Frage kommt, muss jede Frau fÃ¼r sich selbst entscheiden. Aber wenn sich eine Schwangere dafÃ¼r entscheidet, was kommt dann auf sie zu? Kaum jemand weiÃŸ das. Und kaum jemand spricht darÃ¼ber. Abtreibung ist in Deutschland immer noch ein Tabu. Dabei haben im Jahr 2016 rund 100.000 Schwangere in Deutschland abgetrieben. 

FÃ¼r ihre Recherche versucht Ariane sich in eine realistische Situation zu versetzen: Ungewollt schwanger zu sein, und das mit 21 Jahren nach einem One-Night-Stand! 

Darf ich einfach so abtreiben?

Wie man wann abtreiben darf, ist im Paragraf 218 im Strafgesetzbuch geregelt. Ja, Abtreibung ist in Deutschland eine Straftat: â€Wer eine Schwangerschaft abbricht, wird mit Freiheitsstrafe bis zu drei Jahren oder mit Geldstrafe bestraft.â€œ Im Gesetz ist geregelt, unter welchen Bedingungen eine Frau abtreiben kann und dabei straffrei bleibt: 

Zu den Bedingungen gehÃ¶rt zum Beispiel, dass der Abbruch nur durch einen Arzt und nur in den ersten 12 Wochen ab der EmpfÃ¤ngnis durchgefÃ¼hrt werden darf. AuÃŸerdem gilt fÃ¼r die meisten Schwangeren, dass sie an einem staatlich anerkannten BeratungsgesprÃ¤ch teilnehmen mÃ¼ssen. In dem GesprÃ¤ch muss die Frau bestÃ¤tigen, dass sie die Schwangerschaft in eine unzumutbare Notsituation bringen wÃ¼rde. Was eine â€unzumutbare Notsituationâ€œ ist, entscheidet aber nicht die Beraterin, sondern die schwangere Frau.

GrÃ¼nde fÃ¼r Abtreibung laut Pro Familia Beraterin:

Ariane entscheidet sich fÃ¼r ein BeratungsgesprÃ¤ch bei Pro Familia in MÃ¼nchen. Die Beraterin erklÃ¤rt ihr, dass die meisten Schwangeren, die sie wegen einer Abtreibung besuchen, zwischen Ende zwanzig und Mitte dreiÃŸig sind. Einer der wichtigsten GrÃ¼nde sei, das schwangere Frauen kein Kind ohne Vater groÃŸziehen mÃ¶chten. Dazu kommen finanzielle GrÃ¼nde und inzwischen auch die schwierige Wohnungssituation in vielen StÃ¤dten. Laut der Beraterin kommen junge Akademiker zu ihr, die schlicht keinen Platz fÃ¼r ein Kind haben. Sie leben zu zweit in einer Ein-Zimmer-Wohnung, weil sie nichts anderes finden oder eine grÃ¶ÃŸere Wohnung zu teuer ist.

title: These Enchiladas Are a Taste of Real Mexican Home-Cooking | Food Skills
tags: First we feast|"fwf"|"firstwefeast"|"food"|"food porn"|"cook"|"cooking"|"chef"|"kitchen"|"recipe"|"cocktail"|"bartender"|"craft beer"|"complex"|"complex media"|"Cook (Profession)sean evans"|"food skills"|"enchiladas"|"mexican food"|"how to make enchiladas"|"real mexican food"|"el atoradero's"|"tortillas"|"denisse lina chavez"
description:
Covered in chile sauce, and stuffed with meats like chicken or pork, enchiladas are one of Mexico's most beloved culinary exports. At El Atoradero, chef Denisse Lina Chavez drenches her enchiladas in the rich, spice-packed mole found in the city of Puebla. Though taquerias have become ubiquitous in NYC, Chavez prides herself on bringing traditional Mexican cuisine to the five boroughs, following recipes passed down from her grandmother. With fresh tortillas sopped in dark-red mole poblano, El Atoradero's enchiladas are a bucket-list item for Mexican-food fanatics everywhere.

When this young family weighed up their housing options, they wanted something which was non-toxic, environmentally friendly and affordable. A tiny home on wheels was the perfect solution. Teaming up with builder Ben Garratt of Healthy Tiny Homes, their home on wheels was actually constructed as part of a tiny house building work-shop in Vancouver, bringing a sense of community into the project. 

Become a Living Big Patron: https://www.patreon.com/livingbig

The family already has big plans for the home, as they intend to live in it for the next years while renovating a larger home on the property, with the intention of one day gifting the home on wheels to their daughter.

title: Abgelaufene Lebensmittel: Wie lange sind sie wirklich essbar? || PULS Reportage
tags: Abgelaufene Lebensmittel|"abgelaufene Lebensmittel essen"|"Lebensmittel noch haltbar"|"Haltbarkeitsdatum"|"Mindesthaltbarkeit"|"wie lange kann man abgelaufene Lebensmittel noch essen"|"PULS"|"PULS Reportage"|"Webreportage"|"Sebastian Meinberg"|"wie lange sind lebensmittel nach dem verfallsdatum genieÃŸbar"|"Verfallsdatum von Lebensmitteln"|"mindesthaltbarkeitsdatum"|"Lebensmittel-Haltbarkeit"|"kann ich das noch essen?"|"wie lange ist das haltbar?"|"Wissensmagazin"|"Ariane Alter"|"funk"
description:
Sind abgelaufene Lebensmittel noch haltbar? Ist etwas noch essbar, obwohl es das Mindesthaltbarkeitsdatum Ã¼berschritten hat? Sebastian Meinberg fragt sich fÃ¼r PULS Reportage, was das Mindesthaltbarkeitsdatum taugt und untersucht seinen alten KÃ¼hlschrankinhalt im Labor. 

Ist das Kunst oder kann das weg? 
Jeder kennt sie und hat sie vielleicht sogar selbst: KÃ¼hlschrankleichen. Abgelaufenes Pesto oder O-Saft vom letzten Jahr? Bei vielen Leuten landen Lebensmittel mit Ã¼berschrittenem Mindesthaltbarkeitsdatum sofort in der Tonne. Doch sind sie wirklich schlecht oder ist das Haltbarkeitsdatum nur viel zu knapp gewÃ¤hlt? Wie lange kann man abgelaufene Lebensmittel noch essen und woran erkennt man, ob sie noch gut sind? PULS Reportage-Moderator Sebastian Meinberg probiert selbst aus und sucht Antworten in einem Good Food Store, im Labor und in der Politik. 

Das Mindesthaltbarkeitsdatum-MissverstÃ¤ndnis:
In Deutschland steht auf Lebensmitteln entweder ein Mindesthaltbarkeitsdatum oder ein Verbrauchsdatum. Das Mindesthaltbarkeitsdatum bedeutet aber nur: Bis zu diesem Datum garantiert der Hersteller die â€spezifischen Eigenschaftenâ€œ seines Produkts. Danach kÃ¶nnen sich Geschmack, Geruch, Farbe, Konsistenz und NÃ¤hrwert verÃ¤ndern. Essen kann man diese vermeintlich â€abgelaufenen Lebensmittelâ€œ dann noch lange! Das Verbrauchsdatum steht dagegen auf schnell verderblichen Produkten wie Fisch oder Fleisch. Wenn das Verbrauchsdatum ablÃ¤uft, gehÃ¶ren Fisch und Fleisch in die Tonne.

Unser Mindesthaltbarkeitsdatum-Tipp:
Bei Fisch und Fleisch solltet ihr euch immer an das Verbrauchsdatum halten, diese Lebensmittel verderben sehr schnell. Wenn bei Produkten aus dem KÃ¼hlschrank, wie Joghurt oder KÃ¤se, das Mindesthaltbarkeitsdatum Ã¼berschritten ist, gilt: Genau hinschauen und dran riechen. Wennâ€™s gut aussieht und normal riecht, ist es unbedenklich essbar. Und keine Sorge: Solltet ihr euch mal irren, bekommt ihr im schlimmsten Falle Durchfall. Alles, was bei Raumtemperatur verkauft wird, kann ewig halten. Diese Lebensmittel kÃ¶nnt ihr auch nach Ablauf des Mindesthaltbarkeitsdatums gut essen.

description:
Sean Evans and Chili Klaus have joined forces to eat the world's hottest pepper, the Carolina Reaper, not once but twice in their storied history. So you knew that when the Danish thrill-seeker finally stepped into the Hot Ones terror-dome, we couldn't serve him the normal wings of death. Instead, we teamed up with our chili guru Noah Chaimberg to lace the poultry with pure, unadulterated pepper mash from some of the hottest chilies in the world, including the Chocolate Bhutlah (2 million Scoville) and Caramel Reaper. Will the insane duo survive a dab of Reaper Blood, or will this be the end of the road for Sean and Klaus? Find out in this explosive end-of-year Hot Ones special.

description:
This episode of RECIPE?! was inspired by tomatoes! I roasted whole tomatoes with a filling made from pre-made falafels, lentils, parsley, and seasonings. I topped them with some cashew parmesan and got them nice and juicy and crispy on top. The innards of the tomatoes didn't go to waste as I used that to make a delicious fresh tomato sauce. title: IT'S NOT GONNA GET ANY BETTER THAN THIS | VLOG 55
tags: Inthefrow|"In the frow"|"VLOG"|"VLOGGER"|"VLOGGING"|"DAILY VLOG"|"DAILY VLOGGER"|"DAILY VLOGGING"|"WEEKLY VLOG"|"WEEKLY VLOGGER"|"WEEKLY VLOGGING"|"NASA"|"ZEROG"|"ZERO GRAVITY"|"FLORIDA"|"KENNEDY SPACE CENTRE"|"ASTRONAUT"|"ASTRONAUT TRAINING"|"SPACE CENTER"|"SPACE CENTRE"|"OLYMPUS PEN"|"OLYMPUS PEN F"|"zerog"|"IT'S NOT GONNA GET ANY BETTER THAN THIS | VLOG 55"|"the best vlog ever"
description:
ITS NOT GONNA GET ANY BETTER THAN THIS | VLOG 55

There's literally nothing else I could do that is cooler than what we did in this video. This is the best vlog ever that I could have made for this haha! I have been waiting SO long to be able to share this with you and now I finally can; Alex and I did a photoshoot not only at NASA but in zero gravit! This truly was a highlight of my career, being able to create a project like this alongside Olympus for the #olympuspenpassionproject and having the full backing of the team when my idea was so out there, literally! Therefore this vlog partially contains a paid for advertorial in collaboration with Olympus cameras. My childhood dream was always to be an astronaut, so as soon as Olympus approached me I knew I wanted to push the boundaries with this project. I hope you love the experience and result as much as me :) 

The biggest thank you to Olympus, The Kennedy Space Centre and NASA for making all my dreams come true! 


See all the images we shot at NASA here: https://www.inthefrow.com/2017/11/experiencing-childhood-dream-journey-nasa.html

title: Making Chocolate Croissants: Behind Tasty
tags: Tasty|"BuzzFeed"|"BuzzFeed Tasty"|"food"|"crossiant"|"behind the scenes"|"chocolate"|"chocolate croissants"|"breakfast"|"pastry"|"diy"|"do it yourself"|"recipe"|"baking"
description:
Reserve the One Top: http://bit.ly/2v0iast


Here is what you'll need!

Homemade Chocolate Croissants (Pain Au Chocolate)
Servings: 8 

INGREDIENTS 
4 cups flour 
Â½ cup water 
Â½ cup milk
Â¼ cup sugar 
2 teaspoons salt 
1 packet instant yeast 
3 tablespoons unsalted butter, softened
1Â¼ cup cold unsalted butter, cut into Â½-inch thick slices 
1 egg, beaten
2 bars chocolate 

PREPARATION
In a large bowl, mix the flour, water, milk, sugar, salt, yeast, and butter. 
Once the dough starts to clump, turn it out onto a clean counter. 
Lightly knead the dough and form it into a ball, making sure not to over-knead it.
Cover the dough with plastic wrap and refrigerate for one hour. 
Slice the cold butter in thirds and place it onto a sheet of parchment paper..
Place another piece of parchment on top of the butter, and beat it with a rolling pin. 
Keeping the parchment paper on the butter, use a rolling pin to roll the butter into a 7-inch square, Â½-inch thick. If necessary, use a knife to trim the edges and place the trimmings back on top of the butter and continue to roll into a square. 
Transfer the butter layer to the refrigerator.  
To roll out the dough, lightly flour the counter. Place the dough on the counter, and push the rolling pin once vertically into the dough and once horizontally to form four quadrants. 
Roll out each corner and form a 10-inch square. 
Place the butter layer on top of the dough and fold the sides of the dough over the butter, enclosing it completely. 
Roll the dough with a rolling pin to seal the seams, making sure to lengthen the dough, rather than widening it.  
Transfer the dough to a baking sheet and cover with plastic wrap. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Roll out the dough on a floured surface until itâ€™s 8x24 inches. 
Fold the top half down to the middle, and brush off any excess flour.
Fold the bottom half over the top and turn the dough clockwise to the left. This completes the first turn. 
Refrigerate for one hour. 
Roll out the dough again two more times, completing three turns in total and refrigerating for 1 hour in between each turn. If at anytime the dough or butter begins to soften, stop and transfer back to the fridge.  
After the final turn, cover the dough with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight. 
To form the croissants, cut the dough in half. Place one half in the refrigerator. 
Flour the surface and roll out the dough into a long narrow strip, about 8x40 inches. 
With a knife, trim the edges of the dough. 
Cut the dough into 4 rectangles. 
Place the chocolate on the edge of the dough and roll tightly enclosing it in the dough. 
Place the croissants on a baking sheet, seam side down. 
Repeat with the other half of the dough. 
Brush the croissants with the beaten egg. Save the rest of the egg wash in the fridge for later.
Place the croissants in a warm place to rise for 1-2 hours. 
Preheat oven to 400Â°F (200Â°C).
Once the croissants have proofed, brush them with one more layer of egg wash. 
Bake for 15 minutes or until golden brown and cooked through. 
Enjoy warm!

Nun klebst du die flache Seite der zweiten KlammerhÃ¤lfte darauf und presstÂ die beiden Teile zusammen, bis der Kleber getrocknet ist.
Dann kommen die nÃ¤chsten KlammerhÃ¤lften ins Spiel: Klebe sie mit der Innenseite auf beiden Seiten an die KlammerhÃ¤lften, wie auf folgendem Foto gezeigt. Die Schlaufe dient spÃ¤ter dazu, das Werk an den WeihnachtsbaumÂ zu hÃ¤ngen.
Als NÃ¤chstes trÃ¤gst du etwas Kleber unterhalb der Spitze des Dreiecks auf und klebst einen Filzstern darauf. Schon hast du einen festlichen Mini-Baum, den du an den groÃŸen hÃ¤ngen kannst.

Setze nunÂ diesen Filzkreis in die Mitte, gib einen kleinen Klecks Kleber darauf und setze zum Schluss einen Filzstern darauf. Fertig ist der zweite Baumschmuck!

description:
Mit unserem Rezept kannst du den Klassiker Baumkuchen einfach zuhause selber machen!

Den Artikel zum Rezept findest du hier: http://www.leckerschmecker.me/backen-fuer-geduldige/?&ref=yt

DafÃ¼r brauchst du:

FÃ¼r das Marzipan:

175 g gemahlene Mandeln
125 g Puderzucker
2 EL Amaretto

 FÃ¼r den Teig:

100 ml lauwarme Sahne
170 g Butter
225 g Zucker
10 Eier
1 EL Orangenzeste
100 g Maismehl
150 g Mehl

AuÃŸerdem:

300 g Erdbeermarmelade
30 g Butter
200 g geschmolzene, dunkle KuvertÃ¼re
50 g MandelblÃ¤ttchen

So geht es:

Verknete gemahlene Mandeln, Puderzucker und Amaretto zu Marzipan. Sowohl durch das Kneten als auch die WÃ¤rme deiner HÃ¤nde verÃ¤ndert sich die Masse allmÃ¤hlich. FÃ¼r dich bedeutet das, beim Kneten geduldig zu sein. Ist die Masse zu trocken, fÃ¼ge allmÃ¤hlich und sehr sparsam weiteren Amaretto zu.

Zupfe das fertig geformte Marzipan in kleine StÃ¼cke, schÃ¼tte die lauwarme Sahne darauf und mische beides mit einem HandrÃ¼hrgerÃ¤t zu einer Art Creme. Gib Butter und Zucker auf die Creme und rÃ¼hre erneut so lange mit dem HandrÃ¼hrgerÃ¤t, bis du eine gleichmÃ¤ÃŸige Masse erhÃ¤ltst. Trenne die Eier und gib die Eigelbe einzeln und unter weiterem stetigem RÃ¼hren zum Teig. Jetzt reibe Orangenschale in den Teig. Hebe Maismehl und Mehl mit einem Teigschaber unter den Teig. SchlieÃŸlich schlage die Ã¼brigen 10 EiweiÃŸe steif und hebe auch diese unter den Teig.

ErwÃ¤rme die Marmelade und rÃ¼hre sie glatt. Als nÃ¤chstes streichst du eine Springform mit 18 Zentimetern Durchmesser mit Butter aus. Gib eine Kelle Teig in die Form, streiche ihn dÃ¼nn aus und backe ihn fÃ¼r  1 1/2 Minuten in der Grillfunktion bei 220 Â°C, bis der Teig leicht angebrÃ¤unt ist. Bestreiche den Teig dÃ¼nn mit Marmelade und verteile erneut eine dÃ¼nne Schicht Teig. Wiederhole alle Schritte - backen, Marmelade, Teig - bis du 18 Schichten hast oder deine Backform voll ist.

LÃ¶se den gut ausgekÃ¼hlten Kuchen aus der Springform und bestreiche ihn mit KuvertÃ¼re, bis Oberseite und Seiten vollstÃ¤ndig davon bedeckt sind. Streue nun einen Rand aus Mandeln auf den Kuchen in die noch feuchte Schokolade.

title: Chicken Tikka Masala - You Suck at Cooking (episode 69)
tags: chicken|"chicken tikka masala"|"britain"|"india"|"you suck at cooking"|"ysac"|"comedy"|"funny"|"how to"|"chef"|"recipe"|"tutorial"|"tea"
description:
From the creators of Stonehenge; Chicken Tikka Masala. Actually the roots are more complicated than that and Wikipedia explains it better than I can, on account of me not being a historian on this particular subject. 
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chicken_tikka_masala

Subscribe: http://bit.ly/1HuynlY
http://instagram.com/yousuckatcooking
https://twitter.com/yousuckatcookin
Snapchat: @yousuckatcookin 
http://facebook.com/yousuckatcooking

The Recipe
I used two chicken breasts but you could easily do 3 for this recipe, maybe even 4 smaller ones. 
The Marinade:
1/2 cup plain yogurt (full fat)
A teaspoon of garam masala, coriander, cumin, turmeric 
Some salt 
Wangjangle the yogurt and spices together then cube the chicken and slather it all together 
Put it in the fridge from between an hour to overnight
For the sauce dice an onion and fry it in butter or coconut oil
Grate some ginger and garlic and add those in
Add the same spices as before, but slightly more, up to 1.5 teaspoons of each
Add in a large can of crushed tomatoes 
Add in a cup of yogurt
Add in a teaspoon or so of brown sugar if itâ€™s too acidic or you want it slightly sweeter
Add in a teaspoon of salt 
Cook it on low while you broil the chicken
You can also do the chicken in the pan but itâ€™s harder to get even
You also donâ€™t have to cook the chicken until itâ€™s blackened but thatâ€™s what people usually doâ€¦careful not to overcook it
Spread the chicken out on a pan and put your oven on broil and cook it until it just starts to get black
Throw it in the sauce for a few minutes until itâ€™s cooked through
Serve on Basmati rice (or whatever rice you have) 
Chop up some coriander and put it on top 
Bobâ€™s your uncle. In case you didnâ€™t know.

About The Scran Line
Oh hey there! My name is Nick. Iâ€™m a pastry chef and graphic designer. Combine these two passions together and you get The Scran Line! Join me on my baking adventures twice a week I post every Tuesday and Friday.

-

PEACH MACARONS

Makes 30

Macarons
For the macaron shells:
300g almond flour
300g pure icing sugar (without corn flour added to it)
110g liquefied egg whites (see below)
300g caster sugar
75g water
110g liquefied egg whites
2 drops deep pink food gel
Orange colour mist
Pink colour mist
1 tsp peach essence (I bought mine online)

Peach Jelly
3 tsp powdered gelatin
3 tbsp cold water
200g canned peaches (strained)

Frosting
1 batch fluffy vanilla buttercream frosting
1 tsp peach essence
2 drops pink food gel
2 drops orange food gel

title: Earthquake Preparedness Kit
tags: earthquake|"disaster"|"survival"|"survivalist"|"preparation"|"diy"|"do it yourself"|"natural disaster"|"nifty"|"buzzfeed"|"buzzfeed nifty"
description:
Earthquakes occur without warning and can affect everyone in a region within seconds. In the event of the next one causing serious damage, make sure youâ€™re prepared with these handy tips.

Here is what you'll need!

Earthquake Preparedness
Earthquakes are one the world's most deadly natural hazards. Large earthquakes often strike without warning in areas of high population density, which can lead to catastrophic events. 
It is estimated that there are 500,000 detectable earthquakes in the world each year. 100,000 of those can be felt by people, and of those, 100 of them cause damage. 
In the US alone, the NEIC now locates about 20,000 earthquakes each year, or approximately 55 per day.  All 50 states and 5 US territories can get earthquakes, but the risk is higher in identified seismic zones. Some of the areas most at risk include: the San Andreas Fault in California; the Cascadia Subduction Zone in Oregon, Washington, and Alaska; the New Madrid Fault Zone in Missouri, Arkansas, Tennessee, and Kentucky; and smaller East Coast zones such as the mid-Atlantic, coastal South Carolina, and New England

Earthquakes occur without warning and can affect everyone in a region within seconds. Make sure youâ€™re prepared with these handy tips.

EMERGENCY TOILET & SUPPLY KIT

MATERIALS
5-gallon bucket with lid
Pool noodle
Trash bags (minimum 5-gallon capacity)
Toilet paper
2-gallon bucket with lid
Emergency supplies to suit your needs

INSTRUCTIONS
Trim a pool noodle to fit the circumference of the 5-gallon bucket. 
Using a sharp utility knife or sturdy scissors, cut a slit down the length of the pool noodle to open it up. Be careful to only cut through only one side.
Line the bucket with heavy duty trash bags. For safety and hygiene, use at least 2 bags to start.
Fit the pool noodle onto the opening of the bucket, over the bags. 
Pop the steel handle off the side of the bucket. Thread a roll of toilet paper through and pop the handle back into the side.
Fill the smaller 2-gallon bucket with emergency supplies that you and your family will need (donâ€™t forget your pets too!). 
Start with a custom emergency checklist that includes important phone numbers youâ€™ll need, medications, and supplies that youâ€™ll need to check periodically.
Food & water - ideally you should include enough drinking water and shelf-stable, nonperishable food to last you and your family for 72 hours. 
Foods that donâ€™t require cooking or heating are best; and if using canned food, check if you need to also include a can opener! Drop some cutlery in the kit too.
Schedule to check all expiration dates as necessary and remember that water bottles have use-by dates also.
Hand crank portable radio - it may be necessary to rely on news and communication if power is disrupted and lines are down. Include extra batteries.
Portable lighting - flashlights, light sticks or other battery-powered LED lights are best. Avoid candles in case of potential gas hazards. Include spare batteries, and test batteries periodically.
First aid kit and toiletries, including any prescription and over-the-counter medications, glasses, contact lenses and solution etc
Wet hygiene wipes for body and hands and hand sanitizer are useful if the water goes out
Dust mask and gloves
Shelter and warmth - emergency blankets, regular blankets, tarps, even just an old towel, hand warmers
Toolkit - wrench in case you need to shut of gas or water valves, and a multi-purpose tool for general needs.
Store the smaller bucket inside the larger bucket. The pool noodle can be removed from the top and stored inside too, along with the toilet paper. Keep the bucket in a handy location.
Additional and duplicate supplies should be stored separately in easily accessible locations around the house and other frequented places like your car, workplace etc. 

 
QUAKE-PROOFED HOME
Itâ€™s best not to have heavy objects like mirrors or large frames hung or displayed above beds or couches. Otherwise, anchor them in studs or interlocked hooks to prevent them from falling and causing serious injury.
Close hooks from other hanging items by bending them shut with pliers or wrapping them with wire.
Secure precarious furniture such as tall shelves and television screens with furniture straps or L-shaped braces.
Use museum putty or other nonpermanent sticky putty to hold smaller breakables in place.
Alternatively, install low, decorative guardrails across shelves and display units to keep items from sliding off. A simple lip from scrap wood can also do the trick.
Avoid keeping the heaviest items on the top.
Keep a pair of sturdy shoes, a flashlight and even a hard hat under your bed.
Attach velcro to additional flashlights and store them near electrical panels, gas and water valves, and other important utilities for quick access.

description:
Building a DIY arduino/raspberry pi/beaglebone black smart cat feeder for less than $15, we will need:
- 2 cans
- MG996 servo motor
- zip ties
- thick wire
- double bowl
- piece of styrofoam
- electric tape
- arduino or similar microcontroller/microcomputer with PWM support
- something to cut tin with (knife/scissors/dremel).

Also it can be a great cat puzzle if you approach it creatively! My cat pushes the button (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7DwUOdvJp-8) and also gets the food from the interactive stream donations (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6V7L9D9fyVA)

In this video I show you how I made shuriken from a saw blade.  Shuriken are also commonly known as ninja stars.  Shuriken are ancient throwing weapons from Japan.
